F(x) = a x \pmod{b},\text{ where $x$ in $[0,b)$, $a$ and $b$ are co-prime}
\rm\ ax\equiv 0\ \Rightarrow\ x\equiv 0\ \ (mod\ b)\ 
\rm\ x\to ax\ 
\displaystyle ax = ay \mod b
\displaystyle a(x-y) = 0 \mod b
\displaystyle a
\displaystyle b
\displaystyle x-y= 0 \mod b
\displaystyle x = y
\displaystyle x,y \in [0,b)
\displaystyle a \gt b
